In a simple way, the person is explaining that he created a program, inspired by a larger artificial intelligence system called ChatGPT. His code was designed to learn the patterns in the works of Shakespeare and generate new sentences that look like they're from Shakespeare. The goal here is to mimic how the bigger system, ChatGPT, can generate different responses to a given prompt. He calls his program "Nano GPT," and has shared it on a platform named GitHub where other people could use or study it.